{"lemma":"خَطَّ","slug":"خَطَّ","root":"خ.ط.ط","root_slug":"خ-ط-ط","root_link":"/words/roots/خ-ط-ط","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":13},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n10936"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AE%D9%8E%D8%B7%D9%8E%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to draw a line"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to draw"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to write"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to carve, inscribe"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to outline, mark"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of خَطَّ (ḵaṭṭa) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"line","examples":[{"text":"وبالانتقال والفحص تبين تسرب غاز من المواسير الأرضية بخط الغاز الرئيسى المغذى للقرية.","english":"And through the passthrough and the inspection it came to light the leakage of gas from the earth pipes through the main gas supply line of the village."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"stroke"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"stripe"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"ridge"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"handwriting"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"calligraphy"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"script"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Cognate to Nabataean Aramaic 𐢊𐢋𐢋 (“to pull out; to engrave”), Jewish Babylonian Aramaic חֲטַט (ḥăṭaṭ, “to dig out, to hollow out, to excavate”), Classical Syriac ܚܰܛ (ḥaṭṭ, “to dig out; to excavate; to carve”), Akkadian 𒄩𒁕𒂅 (ḫa-ṭa-ṭu /⁠ḫaṭāṭu⁠/, “to dig out; to dredge; to make an incision”)."},"ipa":["/xatˤ.tˤa/","/xatˤtˤ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n10936","headword_ar":"خَطَّ","root":"xT","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaT~N","text_ar":"خَطٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a line,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lines,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a mark,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY AlA^aroDi","text_ar":"عَلَى الاَرْضِ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon the ground."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaT~a Alz~aAjiru fiY AlA^aroDi","text_ar":"خَطَّ الزَّاجِرُ فِى الاَرْضِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor. and inf. n. as above,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The diviner made a line,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a mark,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lines,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"marks, upon the ground, and then divined."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alz~aAjiru yaxuT~u biA_iSobaEihi fiY","text_ar":"الزَّاجِرُ يَخُطُّ بِاـِصْبَعِهِ فِى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~amoli wayazojuru","text_ar":"الرَّمْلِ وَيَزْجُرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The diviner makes lines,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"marks, with his finger upon the sand, and divines"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.) Th says, on the authority of IAar, that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eilomu AlxaT~i","text_ar":"عِلْمُ الخَطِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eilomu Alr~amoli","text_ar":"عِلْمُ الرَّمْلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"geomancy"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: I 'Ab says that it is an ancient science, which men have relinquished: but Lth says that it is practised to the present time; [to which I may add, that it has not even now ceased; being still practised on sand and the like, and also on paper;] and they have conventional terms which they employ in it, and they elicit thereby the secret thoughts &c., and often hit upon the right therein: the diviner comes to a piece of soft ground, and he has a boy, with whom is a style; and the master makes many lines, or marks, in haste, that they may not be counted; then he returns, and obliterates leisurely lines, or marks, two by two; and if there remain two lines, or marks, they are a sign of success, and of the attainment of the thing wanted: while he obliterates, his boy says, for the sake of auguring well,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AibonaYo EiyaAno A^asoriEaA AlbayaAno","text_ar":"اِبْنَىْ عِيَانْ اَسْرِعَا البَيَانْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"O two sons of 'Iyán"},{"kind":"text","text":"(meaning two lines or marks),"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hasten ye the manifestation"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: I 'Ab says that when he has obliterated the lines, or marks, and one remains, it is the sign of disappointment: and AZ and Lth relate the like of this. (TA.) It is said in a trad. of Mo'áwiyeh Ibn-El-Hakam Es-Sulamee, traced up by him to its author,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAna nabiY~N mina","text_ar":"كَانَ نَبِىٌّ مِنَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^anobiyaA='i yaxuT~u famano xaT~ahu Ealima mivola Eilomihi","text_ar":"الاَنْبِيَا=ءِ يَخُطُّ فَمَنْ خَطَّهُ عَلِمَ مِثْلَ عِلْمِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A prophet of the prophets used to practise geomancy; and he who matches his geomancy knows the like of his knowledge"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) You say also, when a man is meditating upon his affair, and considering what may be its issue, or result,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaxuT~u fiY AlA^aroDi","text_ar":"يَخُطُّ فِى الاَرْضِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one makes lines,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"marks, upon the ground"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nakata","text_ar":"نَكَتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and see St. John's Gospel, ch. viii. verses 6 and 8.] And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaT~a birijolihi AlA^aroDa","text_ar":"خَطَّ بِرِجْلِهِ الاَرْضَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He walked,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"went along."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-  Also, (S, Msb,) aor. as above, (Msb,) and so the inf. n., (Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He wrote"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K) a writing, or book, (Msb,) or a thing, (TA,) with the reed prepared for that purpose, (S, K,) or with some other thing; (K, TA;) [and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xT~T","text_ar":"خطّط","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", for]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taxoTiyTN","text_ar":"تَخْطِيطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tasoTiyrN","text_ar":"تَسْطِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or, as in the T,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tsTyr","text_ar":"تسطير"},{"kind":"text","text":"; whence the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuT~iTato Ealayohi *unuwbuhu","text_ar":"خُطِّطَتْ عَلَيْهِ ذُنُوبُهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His sins were written"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"registered"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"against him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaT~a AlxiT~apa","text_ar":"خَطَّ الخِطَّةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaT~ahaA linafosihi","text_ar":"خَطَّهَا لِنَفْسِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see 8; for the latter, in two places. ―         -b4-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaT~a Ealayohi","text_ar":"خَطَّ عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He prohibited it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"took it for himself;"},{"kind":"text","text":"relating to anything. (K, TA.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuT~u waHohuhu","text_ar":"خُطُّ وَحْهُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaT~a","text_ar":"خَطَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see 8. ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaT~a AlgulaAmu","text_ar":"خَطَّ الغُلَامُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see 8. ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaTaTotu biAls~ayofi wajohahu","text_ar":"خَطَطْتُ بِالسَّيْفِ وَجْهَهُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wawasaTahu","text_ar":"وَوَسَطَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I cut,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"clave, with the sword his face and his waist"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaT~ahu biAls~ayofi niSofayoni","text_ar":"خَطَّهُ بِالسَّيْفِ نِصْفَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He clave him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, in halves with the sword"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaAraAhu famaA xaT~a gubaArahu","text_ar":"جَارَاهُ فَمَا خَطَّ غُبَارَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He contended with him in running, and did not cleave his dust."},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, S, * A, L.) ―         -b8-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaT~a A@ll~`hu nawo'ahaA","text_ar":"خَطَّ ا@للّٰهُ نَوْءَهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God made its"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a land's)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rain-giving star"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"asterism"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nawo'N","text_ar":"نَوْءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to pass it over:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"may God make"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]: from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaTiyTapN","text_ar":"خَطِيطَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifying “ a land not rained upon between two lands that have been rained upon: ” (S, TA: *) it was said by I' Ab [in a tropical sense, by way of imprecation, with reference to a woman], when he was asked respecting a man who had put the affair of his wife in her own hand and she had in consequence divorced him by a triple sentence: (S:) accord. to one relation, it is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaT~aA^a","text_ar":"خَطَّاَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; the meaning being “ may he make its rain to miss it: ” (S, TA:) and accord. to another, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaT~aY","text_ar":"خَطَّى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaT~aTa","text_ar":"خَطَّطَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taqaD~aY AlbaAziY","text_ar":"تَقَضَّى البَازِى"},{"kind":"text","text":": the former, or first, is the weaker, or weakest, in authority, of these relations. (TA. [See also 2 in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xTA^","text_ar":"خطا"},{"kind":"text","text":".])"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}